doc.after: Biogeographically New Guinea is part of Australasia rather than the Indomalayan realm although New Guinea s flora has many more affinities with Asia than its fauna which is overwhelmingly Australian Botanically New Guinea considered part of Malesia a floristic region that extends from the Malay Peninsula across Indonesia to New Guinea and the East Melanesian Islands The flora of New Guinea is a mixture of many tropical rainforest species with origins in Asia together with typically Australasian flora Typical southern hemisphere flora include the conifers Podocarpus and the rainforest emergents Araucaria and Agathis as well as tree ferns and several species of Eucalyptus
